                "url": "/topics/interconnected"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654300",
        "quote": "The kind of neuroscience that I do and my colleagues do is almost like the weatherman. We are always chasing storms. We want to see and measure storms - brainstorms, that is.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Miguel Nicolelis",
            "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654300"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Almost",
                "url": "/topics/almost"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654317",
        "quote": "In my view, while the single neuron is the basic anatomical and information processing-signaling unit of the brain, it is not capable of generating behaviors and, ultimately, thinking. Instead, the true functional unit of the central nervous system is a population of neurons, or neural ensembles or cell assemblies.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Miguel Nicolelis",
            "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654317"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Capable",
                "url": "/topics/capable"
            },
            {
                "name": "Functional",
                "url": "/topics/functional"
            },
            {
                "name": "Neural",
                "url": "/topics/neural"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654305",
        "quote": "The brain needs to have a story; it needs to have a logical screenplay telling where we're coming from and what we're going to.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Miguel Nicolelis",
            "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654305"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Going",
                "url": "/topics/going"
            },
            {
                "name": "Needs",
                "url": "/topics/needs"
            },
            {
                "name": "Telling",
                "url": "/topics/telling"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654316",
        "quote": "Essentially, all expressions of human nature ever produced, from a caveman's paintings to Mozart's symphonies and Einstein's view of the universe, emerge from the same source: the relentless dynamic toil of large populations of interconnected neurons.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Miguel Nicolelis",
            "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654316"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Interconnected",
                "url": "/topics/interconnected"
            },
            {
                "name": "Symphonies",
                "url": "/topics/symphonies"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654307",
        "quote": "Eventually, brain implants will become as common as heart implants. I have no doubt about that.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Miguel Nicolelis",
            "url": "/quotes/miguel_nicolelis_654307"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Will",
